      description: 'Give each child a set of five printed toy images in different sizes. Children cut out the toys and arrange them in order from biggest to smallest, then glue them onto a strip of paper in sequence. Below each toy, they write a size word: biggest, bigger, medium, smaller, smallest. Display the size parades on a wall and have children compare their orderings with classmates, discussing whether everyone agreed on the sequence and why size perception can vary.',
