      developmentalNotes: 'Kindergarteners are developing the ability to hold multiple attributes in mind simultaneously, which allows for more sophisticated toy sorting activities. Their growing number sense supports operations with toy counters, and their increasing social awareness makes them interested in comparing their preferences with those of their peers. Data collection activities about toy favorites capitalize on this social curiosity while building foundational statistics skills.',
